interview questions
1.Q: Can EBS be shared across AZ? When do you use EFS?

"EBS is AZ locked вҖ” it can only attach to nodes in the same AZ. For StatefulSet like MySQL, each pod gets its own EBS in its own AZ via volumeClaimTemplates вҖ” they don't share storage, they replicate data via MySQL replication over network. EFS is used when multiple pods across different AZs need to read and write the same files вҖ” like shared media uploads, ML models, or config files. EFS uses ReadWriteMany access mode while EBS uses ReadWriteOnce. In production EKS, I use EBS for databases and EFS for shared application storage."
